records.addlTxt:
Defendant Kimberly M Burnie in court with attorney Robert Gerald Lebell.  Patricia Irene Daugherty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: tmk.  
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.
 
AS TO COUNT 1:
Court ordered defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction concurrent with count 2, 3, 4; release for work, inmate work assignments within the House of Correction, The Day Reporting Center; with credit for 0 days time served. Court notes a strong objection to electronic monitoring. 

AS TO COUNT 2:
Court ordered defendant to serve 4 MONTHS in the House of Correction concurrent with count 1, 3, 4; release for work, inmate work assignments within the House of Correction, The Day Reporting Center; with credit for 0 days time served. Court notes a strong objection to electronic monitoring.

AS TO COUNT 3:
Court ordered defendant to serve 12 MONTHS in the House of Correction concurrent with count 1, 2, 4; release for work, inmate work assignments within the House of Correction, The Day Reporting Center; with credit for 0 days time served. Court notes a strong objection to electronic monitoring.

AS TO COUNT 4:
Court ordered defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction concurrent with count 1, 2, 3; release for work, inmate work assignments within the House of Correction, The Day Reporting Center; with credit for 0 days time served. Court notes a strong objection to electronic monitoring.

COURT STAYED THE SENTENCES and placed defendant on probation for 2 YEARS. Court notes no objection of probation being transferred to county of residence if accepted. 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
- Maintain Absolute Sobriety: No use or possession/use of alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription taken in the manner and fashion as prescribed.
- Defendant to participate in ADOA evaluation, and any additional AODA treatment recommended by DOC
- Department of Corrections must conduct drug and alcohol testing.
- Defendant to notify Department of Corrections agent of all prescriptions within 3 business days/72 hours of receiving prescription from medical professional.
- Fill all prescriptions at one pharmacy, unless otherwise approved by Department of Corrections Agent, and notify the Department of Corrections agent of the pharmacy used. 
- Maintain full time employment/school or a combination of both. 
- If Defendant has any medical treatment, must notify any medical provider of these convictions. 
- Defendant to comply with State Board or medical professional requirements. 
- Defendant to have no employment or volunteer work with access to prescription medications or leave defendant responsible for patient care. 
- Restitution set at $160.00 payable to St. Lukes Hospital Milwaukee, WI as to count 4, due no later than 06-01-2016. Any remaining balance will become immediately due or civil judgment to be entered. 
- Restitution set at ZERO as to count 1, 2, and 3. 
- Fine is set at ZERO.
- Drivers license suspension is not imposed as to count 1 and 3.
- Provide DNA sample, if not already done. 
- Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including the DNA surcharge, during the course of probation to the probation agent. Any remaining balance due /at the end of probation/ will become immediately due or civil judgment to be entered. 

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.

The Court informed the defendant of requirements and penalties applicable under s. 941.29 (1m) or (4m).

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 

Filed;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
